caption: Pre-covid I would give this place 3 stars. It’s a nicer place than your typical American Chinese takeout.  However the food is made for a customer base that can’t handle a wider range of flavors (stuff is bland imho).
Excellent and tasty food, I loved the vibes this spot has, and the staff members were super nice. Will surely visit here next time.
Good food. Great people. Have been dining with family here for years.

Very disappointed. Chicken w Garlic Sauce as bland as i’ve never imagined. A total waste. Scallion Pancakes were reasonably presented so thats the second star. The Financial District is now devoid of any decent Chinese expectations… China chalet where are you?
Chinese food, so great. Had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again.

I dine in this place quite a bit! This is the best place to to have a good dinner.  I visit this place many times. The food is of high quality, the team is polite and the prices are decent. I like eating in this spot to have a good lunch.
One of my main spots to grab something to eat. excellent location, well organised, and excellent customer service. Keep it up!
The food is consistently well prepared and yummy, employees gives awesome service. I like how neat it is and ambience. Will come visit again.
One of my fav places for quality Chinese food.
chinese food and the scene here is better than most. I love this place, great food & service. The staff was friendly and sociable. Prices are decent for the quality.
The place offers an awesome range of delicious food. I like dining here. Employees are always kind, pricing is reasonable and the place is always clean.
Great food!
Chinese food and the atmosphere at this place is great. Great ambiance & decor.
The place offers a large range of fresh food. I like eating here. Employees are always very welcoming, pricing is reasonable and the spot is always clean.
Had a awesome experience in this spot with my girlfriend. The food comes rapidly and the customer service is just excellent. Prices are reasonable.

The price is higher then other Chinese places around. I ordered The shrimp mai fun to go and I just confirmed if there mixed with a vegetable inside or not. My check was 22.80 total and I didn’t pay attention that’s is too much. but what I realized on my way home the lady on reception made a her own add-on for $2 for broccoli :/  that’s I didn’t like. She could inform me about it so I Suggest a “golden chopsticks” place instead.
King pao chicken was excellent. Fried wontons too greasy. Fried rice excellent.

Today I ordered for delivery & I was  disappointed in the portion of food! Me being a grown man & seeing the amount of food that was given to me was so disrespectful! Smh!!!! The portion amount was for a child not an adult! Extremely disappointed! Other than that the food was delicious and I still have an appetite. Smh!!!!!!!!!!!!
I had an extraordinary time at this place. We enjoyed the first-rate vibes and the menu. The staff are super amiable. I’m glad we eventually managed to visit this place.
Very cute and quiet place.  Tucked away from mainstreet traffic. Excellent service delicious food. Had cold sesame noodles and shrimp fried rice.
It's probably the best "sit down" Chinese restaurant in the area with decent food

From the first moment  you step in that restaurant  the stuff gives you an excellent feeling. Very warm hosts, it is a good place to  pass time with friends and colleagues or with your date. heavenly  meals, skillful  chef, competitive  pay and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.

We met with friends at this restaurant for dinner. This restaurant was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The meal was tasty. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. we highly recommend this place.
Wonderful service & positively excellent food!

Omg! I had not had shrimps over angel-hair pasta since long time ago. The wanting for trying it again was there, but never had found a good Chinese restaurant until TODAY! I had the best meal of my life! So tasty, with a hint of spicy, friend eggs and the right amount of soy sauce! Can't complain at all!
(Translated by Google) Good food  (Original) Buena comida
It was average food, poor service,  comparable prices.
Good food. nice place for lunching. you need to reserve a spot if you planned for group lunch.
Reasonably good Chinese food around this area.  Crowded during lunch hours.
Had lunch here with my daughter.  Food was hot and delicious, staff is very attentive.  The food comes out quickly in spite of the fact that its a sit down restaurant with food made to order.
Food was very good.
Best chinese espeacially the beef and broccoli
The best Chinese in NYC
Friendly, fast service. The Singapore Mei fun is fantastic
Food is always good but they got pricey recently. We were very frequent when I worked on wall street.
This place constantly delivers. They serve great food for reasonable pricing, there are no long waits even when the place is loaded.

The food is quite tasty! The reason I'm giving No. 1 a lower rating is because the meals are OVERPRICED LIKE CRAZY. Yesterday, I only ordered shrimp and broccoli with a cup of white rice and it came out to cost $22!!!!! HOLY GUACAMOLE! You are better off going to nearby chinatown Mott st and getting the same meal for half that price! Other restaurants such as the ones at Pearl st are also much, MUCH cheaper. I wouldn't ever tell a business that they should make their meals cheaper so I won't do that. But based on the fact that No. 1 makes such small meals so expensive, I won't ever come back here again.
Would certainly recommend eating here. Exceptional character, tasty dishes, great service. I recommend this place.
I always stop getting some food in here. I enjoyed the prompt customer service and well prepared dishes. 5 stars from me.
Good food fast service
Literally the worst chinese I’ve ever had in my life. So, old and disgusting. Not even worth $5. DEFINITELY not worth $20.
Found 4 strand of short hair in my boyfriend’s food. Never order from her again. He is sick from eating here.

Probably not the number 1 Chinese restaurant in Manhattan but perhaps the best in the immediate Financial District vicinity.  Service is prompt and the food is both consistent and tasty.  It's popular lunch spot in the area but turnover is quick and you won't likely have to wait for a table, though I would call ahead for a large party.

Best Chinese food in the financial district. More expensive, but worth it. There are no lunch specials here but the combination plates serve a similar purpose to lunch specials found elsewhere. They have good vegan and vegetarian options which are recommended. Also, a good spice to their food.  The seating area is also quite nice, as are the waitstaff. Check it out!
Food is delicious but some waiters are rude or their English language is like that.
Fantastic food and service

The food flavor feels light and authentic, but is overpriced.  The waitress will not notify you if two dishes contain the same type of vegetables. You need to ask.  She also asks for tip even after dripping liquid from food on your clothes.
Really good, generous portions, great service.

The food is actually very good. I often order the ribs or spring rolls to start, both are very tasty. There fried rice is plentiful and the meat is decent quality.  They close very early though.  9.30pm is disappointing especially for Manhattan.
I ordered chicken with broccoli  the place looks clean and the food was good.

Ordered on just eat delivery speed was ok about 45 mins. the food was inedible i was very hungry at the time spent 18 pound for myself and couldn't even swallow one mouth full after tasting it 🤢🤮🤮. anyways I gave it to my neighbours as they are pretty hard up for cash and rarely have food in the house they managed to eat it but vomited it back up.  I would not even feed this food to a dog it was that bad
Go to place for office get togethers.
Gone downhill in past year.  Order via Grubhub and past two times our order was missing half of our meal.   And two family members had nasty bouts of diarrhea after eating.... no thx.
horrible this. place is trash
Food was ok.  Hot and sour soup is good.  Expensive.  I ordered combo lunch.  Small amount of fried rice.  Big portion of meat and vegetables.   Egg roll was soggy.  Combo was $15 and soup was $4.
Good place for Chinese foods
Excellent food. Not too much salt and very tasty.  Very busy for lunch, however fast service.
(Translated by Google) Food, price and service very good. Is recommended for New York  (Original) Essen,Preis umd Service sehr gut.Ist für New York zu empfehlen

A average eatery located in the Manhattan financial district serving classic chinese dishes. Visited for lunch today and the experience was ok. I ordered from the lunch offer and my other half went for Thai fish dish. The food was ok and the staff were good, the location was great as it was a short walk once we got off from our cruise.
Outstanding food. Fast and reliable delivery. They have never failed us in 40+ orders to our door
Service is always good, food is always tasty.
Love their hospitality.

The food is ok and pretty pricey. Not a lot of good Chinese options in the area though, so if you work around there you’re kind of stuck. The wonton soup is good. Was not impressed with the sesame chicken.

Awesome little hole in the wall Chinese restaurant that's very underrated. They use unique flavors and preparation styles for an American Chinese restaurant. Try the 5 Spices fish or Garlic beef. A bit pricey for Chinese but totally worth it.
Good food. Combo specials especially
Quality food and good service.
Hole in the wall Chinese restaurant. Ok for a quick bite.
Please never change your food its absolutely delicious and great portion. Thank you😊
Consistent, high quality food and service.

They provided everything we might need in the delivery; paper plates, straws, plasticware, and napkins. What they failed to do was get half of the order correct. I'm a picky eater when it comes to Chinese food so to provide some semi-seafood flavored gravy looking sauce on the side of steamed shrimp and vegetables instead of the garlic shrimp I ordered is a huge let down. Dinner came from the vending machine for me.
Great Plum wine!!! Food was perfectly delicious!!! They even prepared something not on the menu..egg foo young!! Great!!
My go to. Until today. Hair cooked into the chicken

First time trying delivery today. Had eaten there once before a long time ago. Delivery was in under 30 minutes. I had the steamed Chicken and Mixed Vegetables with Garlic sauce on the side. You can order about a half dozen different sauces with this healthy meal. I had the sauce on the side. The food was cooked perfectly and arrived hot. Garlic sauce was average. Delivery man was pleasant.
Food tastes amazing but service is bad.
Ordered mei fun and was quite good, but a little overpriced.

I’m glad I discovered this old-school Chinese restaurant as I was trying to avoid the good-weather crowd on Stone Street. I asked for what was good and ended up with the Szechuan boiled beef. Not for the faint of heart, but awesome and authentic.
Food was so great, and didn't take long to prepare.

Friendly servers! Excellent authentic Chinese food. Food came to the table with great presentation & hot out the kitchen. I ordered the cashew chicken with fried rice. The rice was perfectly cooked; not greasy like many take out places. Loved the atmosphere! Walking distance from Battery Park.
Had dinner.

What great, authentic Chinese Restaurant!!  I went there for the first time yesterday for lunch and had a wonderful experience.  The food was delicious, nice ambiance and good service.  I will definitely go back, must try!!

Just...don’t go. The staff were nice which is why there’s an extra star, but the food...is very below mediocre (not to mention that our utensils were dirty and had visible particles on them). A local cheap Chinese takeout place is way better... this was more expensive (for Chinese food) and served a lower quality food, which was disappointing.
I love the spring rolls, traditional fried rice and lo mein. Food from here makes me nostalgic :)
Good, a little over priced.

I come here a lot with colleagues for lunch. It’s probably the best authentic Chinese food in FiDi - the lunch sets are American Chinese food but the plates are more authentic. Their food tends to be very salty so remember to ask for lower salt when ordering.
Good Chinese food.

I ordered the House Specialty Chicken & Shrimp....it was good & it was hot. It was delivered within 30 minutes. All the condiments were packaged nicely & it even included a paper plate! I will order there again.

I ordered a beef noodle soup. It came up with an instant noodle, even with that flavouring powder. Some meat, but dry and over cooked, looked like some leftover. With $18 for instant noodle + $2 tips, are you going to go there again? No wonder few  customers. Go there only when you can’t find anywhere else.
Adequate Chinese, decent prices. I don't think you'd travel for this one but it'll do if you're working in the area and you have a craving.
Consistent and friendly servers.
Good food!
Pretty decent food for a fair price in the financial district.
Food was pretty Decent and nice staff. A bit small and gets crowded easy

It is No 1, for sure.
The place atmosphere was great. They seated the 10 of us quickly and the food came quickly and it was delicious and hot. 5 stars all the way.
Great Chinese food. Fast

Food is good.  Prices keep going up, up, up.
Got my order wrong and overcharged me.
I ordered the classic chicken and broccoli and chicken steamed dumplings. The dumplings were so soft and delicious. The chicken and broc was also very tasty. Definitely going back here

The food is delicious and portions are HUGE! Prices are not too cheap but you definitely get what you pay for. I have been going there to get takeaway 2 nights in a row and the service is super SPEEDY.
Simply wonderful

Traveled to New York to see Kenny G perform at the Blue Note and he put on a great show. Altogether, tickets, dinner and drinks cost $700.  The food was decent, the staff was rude and absent most of the time. They did push CD's and said that all would be signed by Kenny after the show. We were near the end of the line and as we got closer to Kenny, the club manager barked at his paying customers that we would have to hurry (we stood patiently in line for 15 minutes) because he had people waiting outside in the rain for one and a half hours and needed to get them inside. He obviously mis-managed the line and his staff. What a tremendous let down after a great show. Poor Management.
The food is decent but nothing amazing. The portion size was smaller  than other typical Chinese restaurants for a combo meal.
Service is top notch. Super attentive. Food is super speedy. Prices cheap. Alcohol selection limited though. Wine/beer. Not good wine.
Their food is very good for the most part.  Sometimes the fried rice tastes a little odd like it was burnt.  Spare ribs are a must!
No comment
